# Stages — environment template
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values from your Supabase project's
# API settings page (https://supabase.com/dashboard → Project Settings → API).
#
# These NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are bundled into the browser, which is intended:
# the publishable key is paired with Row Level Security for actual access control.
# Do NOT put service-role / sb_secret_* keys here — those bypass RLS and must
# stay server-side only.

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_your_key_here

# ── Server-side only (set in Vercel project env, NEVER committed with values) ──
# Listed here as NAMES for documentation. Real values live in .env.local (local)
# and the Vercel dashboard (prod). These bypass RLS / authorize privileged
# actions — do not paste actual values into this template.
#
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY   — Supabase service-role key (sb_secret_...). Used by the
#                         API routes (invites, cron) to bypass RLS.
# RESEND_API_KEY        — Resend API key for transactional + founder emails.
# CRON_SECRET           — shared secret for the Vercel Cron → /api/cron/* auth
#                         header. Vercel sends "Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET";
#                         the cron route rejects anything that doesn't match.
# CRON_SECRET=
